pr_body:
The traversal driver executes the requests by traversing internally in the same transaction and with the same connection as the test.

The advantage of the traversal driver is that it does not need uncommitted state to be committed, nor does it commit modifications happening in the request.

// cc @4teamwork/gever @buchi @maethu

Try to unbreak situations where the client goes into an infinite _pagination mode_ when using it with `fetch_list=True`.

```
cs listStorageProviders type=primary page=1
{
  "count": 1,
  "dataStoreProvider": [
    {
      "name": "DefaultPrimary",
      "type": "PRIMARY"
    }
  ]
}

cs listStorageProviders type=primary page=2
{
  "count": 1,
  "dataStoreProvider": [
    {
      "name": "DefaultPrimary",
      "type": "PRIMARY"
    }
  ]
}
```

what could go wrong?

also: https://github.com/ansible/ansible/pull/40233

## Summary

"for strc, in X:" to "for strc in X:" to make this featurizer consistent with BondFractions and BagofBonds that just take a list of Structures.

@WardLT , is it necessary to assume X a list of tuples here?

GetAddressEntry() should return NULL when trying to get an invalid entry;
AppendChlidAddress() should only append valid addresses.
